article.headline: Houston 92, MVSU 58
article.story: HOUSTON -- Kelvin Lewis scored 23 points to lead Houston past winless Mississippi Valley State 92-58 on Saturday night. Marcus Cousin added 18 points and nine rebounds, and Desmond Wade scored 15 points. Aubrey Coleman chipped in 12 points and eight rebounds for the Cougars (6-1). Julius Cheeks was the lone double-digit scorer for the Delta Devils with 23 points. Mississippi Valley State (0-11) shot just 35 percent compared to 53 percent for the Cougars. Houston led 33-24 at halftime and outscored the Delta Devils 59-34 in the second half.
